1ï¸âƒ£ Why useRef exists

Problem first ğŸ‘‡

âŒ Normal variable resets on re-render
function Example() {
  let count = 0;
}


Every render â†’ count = 0 again âŒ

âŒ State causes re-render
setCount(count + 1); // triggers re-render


But sometimes you want to:

store a value

keep it between renders

âŒ NOT re-render the UI

2ï¸âƒ£ What is useRef?

useRef gives you a mutable object that persists across renders but does NOT cause re-render when changed.

3ï¸âƒ£ Basic syntax
const myRef = useRef(initialValue);


Returns:

{
  current: initialValue
}

4ï¸âƒ£ MOST COMMON use case â€” DOM access
function InputFocus() {
  const inputRef = useRef(null);

  return (
    <>
      <input ref={inputRef} />
      <button onClick={() => inputRef.current.focus()}>
        Focus Input
      </button>
    </>
  );
}

Whatâ€™s happening?

React puts DOM element into inputRef.current

No re-render happens

You directly access DOM

5ï¸âƒ£ useRef vs useState (VERY IMPORTANT)
useState	useRef
Triggers re-render	âŒ No re-render
For UI data	For non-UI data
Async update	Sync update
6ï¸âƒ£ Storing previous value (common interview Q)
function Counter({ value }) {
  const prevValue = useRef(value);

  useEffect(() => {
    prevValue.current = value;
  });

  return (
    <p>
      Current: {value}, Previous: {prevValue.current}
    </p>
  );
}

7ï¸âƒ£ useRef for timers / intervals
const timerRef = useRef(null);

useEffect(() => {
  timerRef.current = setInterval(() => {
    console.log("running");
  }, 1000);

  return () => clearInterval(timerRef.current);
}, []);

8ï¸âƒ£ Why not use state here?
setTimer(timer); // âŒ causes re-render unnecessarily


Refs are escape hatches for React.

9ï¸âƒ£ Very important misconception âŒ

âŒ Changing ref.current updates UI

NO âŒ
UI updates only on state/props change

ğŸ”Ÿ Mental model ğŸ§ 

Think of useRef as:

A box that React never looks into for rendering

ğŸ¯ Interview questions

Q: Does useRef cause re-render?
A: No.

Q: When should you use useRef instead of state?
A: When value is needed across renders but doesnâ€™t affect UI.

